item.title: Gun Violence
item.description: Following the outbreak of COVID-19, the Black Lives Matter movement brought attention to police violence against the Black community and the people overall, with protests spanning the globe bringing additional scrutiny and evidence against long-established practices. A wealth of information has followed, including self-recorded videos and data, allowing us to connect systemic-level violence with the intensity of individual shootings that some may have dismissed as anecdotal.
